类 DensityPeaks

  • java.lang.Object
    • clustering.Clustering
      • clustering.DensityClustering
        • clustering.DensityPeaks

  • public class DensityPeaks
extends DensityClustering
    The density peaks clustering algorithms.

    Author: Fan Min minfanphd@163.com, minfan@swpu.edu.cn
    Copyright: The source code and all documents are open and free. PLEASE keep this header while revising the program.
    Organization: Lab of Machine Learning, Southwest Petroleum University, Chengdu 610500, China.
    Project: The cost-sensitive active learning project.

    Progress: The simple version finished. Kernels may be added in the future
    Written time: April 10, 2019.
    Last modify time: July 21, 2019.

                    int paraDistanceMeasure,

        The constructor for independent running.
        参数:
        paraFilename - The data set filename.
        paraDistanceMeasure - The distance measure as an object.
        paraDcScheme - The dc scheme. DIAMETER_FOR_DC or AVERAGE_FOR_DC.
        paraDcRatio - The ratio for radius computation.
        paraKernel - The kernel, cutoff or Gaussian.

      • clusterInTwo

        public int[][] clusterInTwo(int[] paraBlock,
                            int[] paraQueriedArray)
                     throws UnableToClusterInKException
        Cluster the given block in two using density peaks. May change later to obtain balanced clusters.
        覆盖:
        clusterInTwo 在类中 Clustering
        参数:
        paraBlock - The given block.
        paraQueriedArray - The queried instance within the block. The indices should be a subset of [0 .. paraBlock.length - 1].
        返回:
        Two blocks
        抛出:
